This is a JNI implementation for the miniLZO C API

See http://www.oberhumer.com/opensource/lzo/ to have fresh C sources.

Operating Systems :

This library has been compiled under Linux (64Bits) and Windows (32Bits, 64Bits) 
operation system. The jar library tries to load the dll/library in a temporary 
folder.


How to compile :

Windows :
---------

Install MINGw
Install MINGw64
Install a JDK in a path containing no space characters
Declare in env PATH , MINGW exec + your JDK bin folder

Linux :
-------

run linux_build.sh under linux system

Building the jar :
------------------

run the jar ant target (build.xml located in project folder)

Testing the library:
--------------------

Once the jar is build, you can launch TestLZOJni java program.